    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 898.00/578.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese National Association</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco, Cal.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chinese National Association, representing four-fifths of the Chinese
                    residents of the United States, British Columbia and Mexico, earnestly requests
                    the United States Government to use its best offices to maintain and preserve
                    the neutrality of the powers toward the revolutionary struggle now in progress
                    in China, in order that her integrity may be preserved and a stable government
                    established.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Chinese National Association</hi>, <lb/> By <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tong King Chong</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
